{"book": {"publisher": "Alfred a Knopf Inc", "synopsis": "The extraordinary #1 New York Times bestseller that is now a major motion picture, Markus Zusak"s unforgettable story is about the ability of books to feed the soul.<br/><br/>It is 1939. Nazi Germany. The country is holding its breath. Death has never been busier, and will become busier still.<br/><br/>Liesel Meminger is a foster girl living outside of Munich, who scratches out a meager existence for herself by stealing when she encounters something she can’t resist–books. With the help of her accordion-playing foster father, she learns to read and shares her stolen books with her neighbors during bombing raids as well as with the Jewish man hidden in her basement.<br/><br/>In superbly crafted writing that burns with intensity, award-winning author Markus Zusak, author of I Am the Messenger, has given us one of the most enduring stories of our time.", "language": "en", "image": "https://images.isbndb.com/covers/10/03/9780375831003.jpg", "title_long": "The Book Thief", "edition": "Reprint", "dimensions": "Weight: 1.55 Pounds", "dimensions_structured": {"weight": {"unit": "pounds", "value": 1.55}}, "pages": 560, "date_published": "2006", "subjects": ["Children's Books', 'Growing Up & Facts of Life', 'Family Life', 'Literature & Fiction', 'Historical Fiction', 'Contemporary', 'Teen & Young Adult', 'Social & Family Issues', 'Holocaust'], 'authors": ["Markus Zusak'], 'title": "The Book Thief", "isbn13": "9780375831003", "msrp": 19.99, 'binding": "Hardcover", "isbn": "0375831002", "isbn10": "0375831002"}}